415.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/eux1701568186415.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/eux1701568186415.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"eux1701568186415\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Cleans up the widget when it is unbound from a data object.</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">dataCleanup(dataNames)</code></p>\n<p class=\"p\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Arguments</strong></p>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">dataNames</code></p>\n<p class=\"p\">A Set containing the names of all properties that were changed through\n\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">dataUpdate()</code> calls since this widget was connected to this data\n\t\t\tobject.</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Exceptions</strong></p>\n<p class=\"p\">None</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Return value</strong></p>\n<p class=\"p\">None</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Description</strong></p>\n<p class=\"p\">The framework calls the <code class=\"ph codeph\">dataCleanup()</code> function to give the widget an\n\t\t\topportunity to clean up its data-related internals. The widgets are reused by the\n\t\t\tframework, so it is important that they clear up after themselves to avoid bugs. This\n\t\t\tfunction's argument describes the names of all properties that were changed through\n\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">dataUpdate()</code> calls since this widget was connected to this data\n\t\t\tobject when its <code class=\"ph codeph\">dataInit()</code> function was called. The\n\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">dataNames</code> argument is a set of strings with the following\n\t\t\tproperties:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104eux1701568186415_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"eux1701568186415__codeblock_n12_b4j_qzb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">Set(n){\n      \"prop_id\",\n      \"html:prop_id\",\n      \"style:prop_id\",\n      \"class:class_name\",\n      \"valrep\",\n      \"value\"   \n      } \n Where n is the number of properties in the set.       \n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5442454\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5442454\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "dataCleanup Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Feb 25, 2026 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Cleans up the widget when it is unbound from a data object. dataCleanup(dataNames) Arguments dataNames A Set containing the names of all properties that were changed through dataUpdate() calls since this widget was connected to this data object. Exceptions None Return value None Description The framework calls the dataCleanup() function to give the widget an opportunity to clean up its data-related internals. The widgets are reused by the framework, so it is important that they clear up after themselves to avoid bugs. This function's argument describes the names of all properties that were changed through dataUpdate() calls since this widget was connected to this data object when its dataInit() function was called. The dataNames argument is a set of strings with the following properties: Explain this code Set(n){ \"prop_id\", \"html:prop_id\", \"style:prop_id\", \"class:class_name\", \"valrep\", \"value\" } Where n is the number of properties in the set. Copy Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}